@startuml UC-03_Build_Workflow_Canvas_Sequence

title UC-03: Build Workflow Canvas - Sequence Diagram

skinparam SequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam SequenceArrowColor #00796B
skinparam ActorBackgroundColor #E0F2F1
skinparam ParticipantBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam SequenceGroupBackgroundColor #FFF9C4

actor User
participant Canvas
participant Frontend
participant "API Gateway" as API
participant WorkflowService
participant Database as DB
participant ValidationService

User -> Canvas: 1. Open Workflow Canvas
Canvas -> Frontend: 2. Load canvas editor
Frontend -> API: 3. GET /api/v1/workflows/{id}/nodes
API -> WorkflowService: 4. get_workflow_nodes(workflow_id)
WorkflowService -> DB: 5. Fetch nodes data
DB --> WorkflowService: 6. Return nodes []
WorkflowService --> API: 7. Nodes list
API --> Frontend: 8. 200 OK + nodes
Canvas --> User: 9. Display empty/existing canvas

User -> Canvas: 10. Drag trigger component
Canvas --> Canvas: 11. Add trigger node
User -> Canvas: 12. Click node to configure
Canvas -> User: 13. Show configuration panel

User -> Canvas: 14. Set node type (e.g., "Send Email")
User -> Canvas: 15. Configure parameters
Canvas --> Canvas: 16. Update node config in memory

User -> Canvas: 17. Click "Add Another Node"
Canvas --> Canvas: 18. Add new node to canvas
User -> Canvas: 19. Position nodes

User -> Canvas: 20. Draw connection (edge)
Canvas --> Canvas: 21. Create edge between nodes
Canvas -> Frontend: 22. Validate edge connection

Frontend -> ValidationService: 23. validate_edge(source, target)
ValidationService --> Frontend: 24. Edge valid
Canvas --> Canvas: 25. Visual feedback: edge created

User -> Canvas: 26. Click "Add Condition"
Canvas -> User: 27. Show condition builder
User -> Canvas: 28. Configure condition logic
Canvas --> Canvas: 29. Store condition on edge

User -> Canvas: 30. Add variables (if needed)
Canvas -> User: 31. Show variable panel
User -> Canvas: 32. Enter variable name & type
Canvas --> Canvas: 33. Add to workflow variables

User -> Canvas: 34. Test the workflow
Canvas -> Frontend: 35. Collect canvas data
Frontend -> API: 36. POST /api/v1/workflows/{id}/test
note right of API
  Body: {
    "nodes": [...],
    "edges": [...],
    "variables": {...},
    "testData": {...}
  }
end note

API -> WorkflowService: 37. test_workflow(workflow_id, data)
WorkflowService -> ValidationService: 38. Validate workflow structure
ValidationService --> WorkflowService: 39. Structure valid

WorkflowService -> DB: 40. Execute test run (no persistence)
activate DB
DB --> WorkflowService: 41. Test execution completed
deactivate DB

WorkflowService --> API: 42. Return {status, logs, results}
API --> Frontend: 43. 200 OK + test results
Canvas --> User: 44. Display test results

User -> Canvas: 45. All looks good, save workflow
Canvas -> Frontend: 46. Collect all canvas changes
Frontend -> API: 47. PUT /api/v1/workflows/{id}/save
note right of API
  Body: {
    "nodes": [...],
    "edges": [...],
    "variables": {...}
  }
end note

API -> WorkflowService: 48. update_workflow(workflow_id, data)
WorkflowService -> ValidationService: 49. Validate complete workflow
ValidationService --> WorkflowService: 50. All validations pass

WorkflowService -> DB: 51. UPDATE workflow document
activate DB
DB --> WorkflowService: 52. Saved successfully
deactivate DB

WorkflowService -> DB: 53. Increment version number
DB --> WorkflowService: 54. Version updated

WorkflowService --> API: 55. Return {status: "saved"}
API --> Frontend: 56. 200 OK + save confirmation
Canvas --> User: 57. Show "Workflow Saved" notification

@enduml
